<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910517-0121</DOCNO><DOCID>910517-0121.</DOCID><HL>   Navistar Posts a Loss</HL><DATE>05/17/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   NAV</CO><MS>INDUSTRIAL (IDU)</MS><IN>EARNINGS (ERN)LAND TRANSPORT EQUIPMENT, RAILCARS, BUSES (LDT)ALL TRANSPORTATION EQUIPMENT (TRQ)</IN><NS>EARNINGS (ERN)</NS><RE>ILLINOIS (IL)</RE><LP>   CHICAGO -- Navistar International Corp., hurt by acontinuing industry downturn, reported a loss of $29 million,or 15 cents a share, for its second quarter ended April 30.   The loss came on an 8.3% decline in sales, to $940million. In the year-earlier period, the maker of trucks andheavyduty engines had earnings of $8 million, or one cent ashare, on sales of $1.03 billion.</LP><TEXT>   Navistar said its results &quot;continue to be adverselyaffected by lower industry-wide demand for medium and heavytrucks, and midrange diesel engines.&quot;</TEXT></DOC>